1 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES - FLOOR VERSION
2 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
3 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026)
4 HOUSE
RESOLUTION 1055 By: Patzkowsky
5
6
7 AS INTRODUCED
8 A Resolution declaring April 29, 2026, as Oklahoma
Agriculture Day; recognizing and celebrating
9 agriculture's impact on Oklahoma's heritage and
economy; and directing distribution.
10
11
12 WHEREAS, agriculture is one of Oklahoma's leading industries and
13 its associated production, processing, and marketing sectors
14 combined provide nearly 200,000 jobs and contribute more than $28
15 billion to our state's economy; and
16 WHEREAS, Oklahoma ranks fourth nationally with more than 69,700
17 farms and ranches, utilizing 32.8 million acres of Oklahoma's rich
18 land to provide food, fiber, and other necessities of life to
19 Oklahomans and people across the world; and
20 WHEREAS, Oklahoma is known as the nation's premier spot for
21 wheat production and research, ranking third for winter wheat
22 bushels harvested annually; and
23 WHEREAS, Oklahoma is also America's second-leading provider of
24 beef cows with nearly two million head and the third-most cattle
HR1055 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 oper ations at more than 43,000, featuring over 4.65 million beef and
2 dairy cattle; and
3 WHEREAS, Oklahoma also ranks as the second top provider of rye
4 nationally and is one of the highest producers of soybeans, cotton,
5 poultry, and pork in the United States; and
6 WHEREAS, agriculture provides a major source of employment for
7 Oklahoma's workforce, with 1-in-50 jobs supported by the pork
8 industry and another 30,000 people employed by the poultry industry
9 as just two examples of the vast reach and importance of agriculture
10 in our state; and
11 WHEREAS, the agriculture industry's success is vital to
12 maintaining the strength of Oklahoma's economy, the standard of
13 living for our citizens, and our presence in the world trade market;
14 and
15 WHEREAS, it is important for all Oklahomans to understand the
16 role agriculture plays in their daily lives, whether they live in
17 urban or rural areas.
18 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
19 OF THE 2ND SESSION OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE:
20 THAT the Oklahoma House of Representatives declares April 29,
21 2026, as Oklahoma Agriculture Day at the Capitol.
22 THAT the Oklahoma House of Representatives recognizes and
23 celebrates agriculture's impact on our state's heritage and economy.
24
